, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Usamah ibn Zayd reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would put me on one of his thighs and he would put Hasan ibn Ali on his other thigh. Then, the Prophet would hug us and he would say, \u201cO Allah, be merciful to them as\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3927,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/31\/assume-prophet-righteous\/","url_meta":{"origin":20383,"position":2},"title":"Ali on Hadith: Assume the Prophet is most righteous, guided","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 31, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Abdur Rahman reported: Ali ibn Abi Talib, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhen I narrate to you a tradition from the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, assume from it that he is the most proper, the most guided, and the most righteous.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":9897,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/11\/22\/ali-ibn-abi-talib-harun-musa\/","url_meta":{"origin":20383,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Prophets: Ali is to Muhammad as Aaron to Moses","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 22, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019d ibn Abi Waqqas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, set out to Tabuk and he left Ali behind. Ali said, \"You leave me behind with the women and children?\" The Prophet said, \"Are you not pleased in the same position for me as Aaron\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5232,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/16\/prophet-walks-sahabah-ride\/","url_meta":{"origin":20383,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Humility: The Prophet walks, his companions ride","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 16, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: On the day of Badr, we were riding with three men upon one camel. Abu Lubabah and Ali ibn Abi Talib were the two riding with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him. It was time for the Messenger of Allah to walk,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28834,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/08\/hasan-husayn-two-sweet-basils\/","url_meta":{"origin":20383,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Husayn: Hasan and Husayn are my two sweet-basils","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Nu\u2019m reported: I watched Ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, as he was asked about a man killing mosquitoes. Ibn Umar said, \u201cWhere are you from?\u201d The man said, \u201cThe people of Iraq.\u201d Ibn Umar said, \u201cLook at this man! He asks me about killing mosquitoes\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u062